3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Paradex implements 1-hour funding intervals for RUNE/USDT, significantly more frequent than traditional 8-hour cycles. The funding rate is calculated based on the premium/discount between the perpetual contract price and the underlying RUNE spot price. Traders pay or receive funding every hour at the top of the hour, with rates determined by the weighted average price differential over the preceding period. Portfolio margin capabilities allow efficient capital utilization across multiple positions."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","RUNE","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"RUNE represents THORChain's native token, making it sensitive to cross-chain liquidity dynamics and DeFi protocol developments. The token's volatility and correlation with broader DeFi sentiment create frequent funding rate imbalances. Mid-tier volume on Paradex provides opportunities for smaller arbitrage positions without significant market impact."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"RUNE/USDT funding rates on Paradex exhibit pronounced cycles correlating with THORChain protocol updates and cross-chain volume fluctuations. During DeFi bull runs, positive funding rates often exceed 0.1% per hour as leveraged longs accumulate. Conversely, protocol concerns or broader market downturns drive negative rates below -0.05% hourly. The 1-hour funding frequency amplifies these movements compared to 8-hour cycles on CEXs. Weekend periods typically show reduced volatility in funding rates due to lower institutional participation."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"The most consistent arbitrage opportunities arise from funding rate divergence between Paradex and centralized exchanges like Binance or OKX. RUNE's mid-tier liquidity creates temporary disconnects between DEX and CEX funding rates, especially during volatile periods. Self-custodial nature eliminates counterparty risk while enabling delta-neutral strategies across venues. Portfolio margin on Paradex allows leveraging multiple pairs simultaneously, creating sophisticated arbitrage structures. Early-stage status means fewer sophisticated arbitrageurs, potentially leaving inefficiencies unexploited longer."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"StarkNet's complexity introduces unique technical risks including potential network congestion and withdrawal delays during high activity. Paradex's early-stage development means limited track record and possible smart contract vulnerabilities. RUNE's exposure to THORChain protocol risk adds fundamental uncertainty beyond typical perpetual trading risks. Limited pair coverage restricts hedging options compared to mature exchanges. Gas costs on StarkNet, while generally lower than Ethereum mainnet, can impact profitability of small arbitrage positions during network congestion."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How does Paradex's 1-hour funding interval affect RUNE arbitrage strategies?","answer":"The 1-hour intervals create more frequent rebalancing opportunities but require active monitoring. Funding payments occur 24 times daily versus 3 times on traditional 8-hour cycles, amplifying both profits and losses from rate movements."},{"question":"What are the main risks of holding RUNE perpetuals on Paradex?","answer":"Primary risks include StarkNet network issues, smart contract vulnerabilities due to early-stage development, and THORChain protocol risks affecting RUNE's fundamental value. Additionally, limited liquidity may cause slippage during position exits."},{"question":"How does portfolio margin work for RUNE funding rate arbitrage on Paradex?","answer":"Portfolio margin calculates risk across all positions collectively, reducing margin requirements for hedged strategies. This allows efficient capital usage when running delta-neutral arbitrage between RUNE and other assets on the platform."},{"question":"Can I arbitrage RUNE funding rates between Paradex and CEXs?","answer":"Yes, but consider withdrawal times from StarkNet and potential basis risk between venues. The self-custodial nature eliminates counterparty risk but adds operational complexity compared to CEX-to-CEX arbitrage."}]}]
